<br>
Firstly, no-one likes loosing good members to go join the uber guilds.  As someone who has lost members, i know that it is disappointing, especially if your guild has helped get them to the level where they can join an uber guild.  However, it happens, and people need to develop their characters. I wish everyone who has left our guild good luck in their applications to their new guilds.<br>
Second, gearing characters then selling them sucks.  The guild will work hard to get people kitted out, to sell the account afterwards is a real slap in the face.  <br>
<br>
The important distinction is the subterfuge.  If you are thinking of quiting and selling, let your guild leaders know.  They will then know not to bother getting you the uber gear.  But if you actively work to get gear to enhance your market value for a sale, you are decieving your guild.<br>
<br>
Telling your guild you are going to leave and getting geared up is not ideal.  Getting geared up and then leaving guild without a word is bad.  Getting geared up and then selling your character is terrible.<br>
<br>
It does seem harsh that the new popermen is being punished for the old popermen's approach.  It seems unfair, as it was never publicised in advance that ex sold Wudan accounts would be KOS.  From now on i suppose people should know not to buy wudan accounts.<br>
Of course, the best way would be not to buy accounts at all, and just level up. <p>Bollix Braker <BR> 
